in: 0 0 20px 0;">Airbnb picked the right asymptoting curves &#8211; more su=
pply kept delivering more defensibility. When Wimdu tried to compete with i=
t in Europe, Airbnb won because its scale drove cross-border network effect=
s. Airbnb picked a business in which getting to scale fast mattered, and th=
en got to scale fast before the window closed.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64=
, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>L=
ooking for curves that take a long time to asymptote is a good rule of thum=
b when evaluating network effects, switching costs, and scale economies in =
</span><em>any</em><span> industry: </span><strong>once you&#8217;re runnin=
g in the right direction, how far can out-executing your competitors take y=
ou?&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>No matter which industry you&=
#8217;re entering, if you get to this point in the diagnosis and the best p=
otential moat you can come up with is </span><strong>brand</strong><span> o=
r </span><strong>process power</strong><span>, you might be in trouble. Bot=
h take a very long time to develop, if they do at all, and when they do, it=
&#8217;s often through some emergent magic.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"col=
or: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0=
;"><strong>Cornered resources</strong><span> are also tricky, but not impos=
sible, to acquire. </span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">So before you launch, and d=
efinitely before you raise money, figure out whether you think you can crea=
te scale economies, switching costs, maybe network effects, or mayyybe corn=
ered resources before your uncertainty window closes.&#160;</p><p style=3D"=
color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20p=
x 0;">But what if that&#8217;s not enough time? What if you&#8217;re enteri=
ng a market that already has competitors?&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>=
My favorite power &#8211; </span><strong>counter-positioning</strong><span>=
 &#8211; might be able to help. Counter-positioning isn&#8217;t a forever m=
oat, but it can be really useful in extending your window until you can dig=
 one.&#160;</span><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/bcd07a15-9909=
-4b2d-bcf9-d45112c58901?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbq=
Osa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: unde=
rline;">Ramp</a><span> </span><strong>counter-positioned</strong><span> bea=
utifully in corporate cards. I wrote about it </span><a href=3D"https://lin=
k.sbstck.com/redirect/94ccae13-77a3-4df4-a46a-bb682098f3d4?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb=
