lative;"><strong>Good Strategy at Breather</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: =
rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><=
strong>Diagnosis</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size:=
 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">In late 2017, Breather opera=
ted roughly 400 spaces in ten markets after expanding way too quickly based=
 on incorrectly analogizing ourselves to Uber (every startup&#8217;s strate=
gy is unique!). We set a goal to add a space every day, and we did it, even=
 if it meant adding spaces that weren&#8217;t ideal. That left us with too =
many spaces that didn&#8217;t fill up and lost money. As a result, our gros=
s margins across the network sat at -25%.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(6=
4, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">At the=
 time, we only let customers book hourly bookings up to a full day through =
our app. Customers were asking us if they could rent spaces for longer peri=
ods &#8211; a month or more &#8211; but we told them that&#8217;s not what =
we do. Better-funded competitors like WeWork and Knotel focused exclusively=
 on these relatively longer bookings, and we didn&#8217;t want to compete w=
ith them directly.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Doing the hardest and least l=
ucrative bookings, we developed a unique set of strengths. Our operations t=
eam could turn a space in 30 minutes. Our data science team could dynamical=
ly price spaces based on real-time demand signals. Our design, construction=
, and launch teams were used to high-volume, short timeline space launches.=
 Users booked through an app, on-demand, and accessed the space with their =
phone. They used spaces for a number of different use cases &#8211; meeting=
s, brainstorms, focused work, events &#8211; often requiring different conf=
igurations. We coordinated everything through our in-house backend system.&=
#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Based on those strengths, and the clear margin c=
hallenge, we identified a couple of core challenges to focus on.&#160;</p><=
ol style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"=
><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">We n=
eeded to fill our space inventory more consistently to improve margins.&#16=
0;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: bord=
er-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">We could move upmarket into month=
ly bookings much more easily than WeWork and Knotel could move downmarket i=
nto private, on-demand hourly bookings.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: =
8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-le=
ft: 4px;">We might be able to counter-position to buy ourselves time to cre=
ate switching costs.&#160;</p></li></ol><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);=
 font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">With that diagnos=
is in-hand, we set out a guiding policy.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64=
, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong=
>Guiding Policy</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Our guiding policy was simple=
: offer growing startups a network of flexible spaces that grows with their=
 needs instead of one single office. To do that, we would make every space =
in our network available for as little as an hour and as long as a year, pr=
iced in real-time based on demand.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, =
64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">If a space wa=
s underperforming as an hourly space, we could make it available as a month=
ly office for a lower price than our competitors: turning a space from nega=
tive to breakeven improved the network&#8217;s margins, and pushed its dema=
nd into nearby strong-performing hourly spaces, juicing their margins. If a=
 customer rented a space for a month+, we could offer them discounts on nea=
rby spaces, allowing them to spend less on a permanent space and flex up wh=
en they needed more room to host an important meeting, have a sensitive con=
versation, or a place to work when they traveled to another one of our mark=
ets.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Instead of viewing each space independently=
, we viewed the whole network as one big office that responded to our custo=
mers&#8217; needs on-demand.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><strong>Coherent Ac=
tions</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Actually pulling that off was insanely =
difficult and required intense execution from the team.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">As just a few examples, we needed to:&#160;</p><ul style=3D"margi=
n-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-forma=
t: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left:=
 4px;">Update our pricing models to dynamically price spaces both hourly an=
d monthly.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-for=
mat: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-lef=
t: 4px;">Retrain our BD team to sell monthly spaces and trust the data scie=
nce team&#8217;s pricing when selling, and re-orient their quotas around mo=
nth+ sales targets.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-sp=
ecial-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; pa=
dding-left: 4px;">Update our website and app to enable both hourly and mont=
hly bookings on the frontend, with live prices and availability updated hou=
rly.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: b=
ullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-si=
ze: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px=
;">Redo our backend system - Backstage - to account for both hourly and mon=
thly bookings.</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-forma=
t: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left:=
 4px;">Design spaces that could be flipped between hourly and monthly booki=
ngs within a day to minimize dead time, and rework our launch and logistics=
 processes to transform spaces in that day.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"marg=
in: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: bord=
er-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin:=
 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Source new furniture from oversea=
s and design some of our own to facilitate that switching.&#160;</p></li><l=
i style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"b=
ox-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height=
: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Retrain our operat=
ions team to clean and maintain both hourly and monthly bookings. After an =
hourly booking, a space needs a full reset; when it&#8217;s someone&#8217;s=
 office, they want it to be clean but they want their things exactly where =
they left them.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-specia=
l-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; paddin=
g-left: 4px;">Use our pricing models to inform the real estate team&#8217;s=
 new space acquisitions. Because of our mix of bookings and the on-demand n=
ature, we had the most real-time commercial real estate pricing data, and u=
sed it to inform an underwriting model that predicted a space&#8217;s reven=
ue to 95%+ accuracy.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-s=
pecial-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, =
64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; p=
adding-left: 4px;">Lease larger spaces, and cluster more spaces near each o=
ther to give month+ customers convenient access to different space types wh=
en they needed.&#160;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-specia=
l-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 6=
4); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; paddin=
g-left: 4px;">Change the way that access codes worked so that monthly clien=
ts didn&#8217;t need to inform their teams of a new code every day.&#160;</=
p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p s=
tyle=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Train our=
 customer care team to work differently with hourly and monthly clients.&#1=
60;</p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"=
><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">Upda=
te our marketing to reflect our new value proposition, and to create leads =
for the sales team instead of driving everything to in-app on-demand bookin=
gs.&#160;</p></li></ul><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Each one of these actions alone, o=
r in the hands of competitors, wouldn&#8217;t have done much good. Together=
, they built a machine that had a momentum of its own.&#160;</p><p style=3D=
"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20=
px 0;">There were a thousand more things that the team did to put the new s=
trategy into action, but that gives you a flavor. Half the battle was being=
 clear about what we were trying to do, and why, and pointing out that we w=
ere the only ones who could do it. The vast majority of the coherent action=
s that the team took didn&#8217;t come from Ben and I; they came from the t=
eam.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">That year was the most exhilarating of my s=
ix at Breather. We moved so fast. People stayed at the office late and chee=
red every time a gong ring announced a monthly booking.&#160;</p><p style=
=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 20px 0;">And it worked. Our margins flipped from -25% to +25% in six month=
s. WeWork and Knotel didn&#8217;t respond, and we were able to steal custom=
ers from them. They were still much bigger than us, but we offered somethin=
g unique.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; lin=
e-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Unfortunately, we didn&#8217;t get the=
 chance to see whether the strategy would have created long-term defensibil=
ity. We threw it out when the new exec team joined in 2019, focusing solely=
 on plain vanilla monthly bookings. Who knows if our strategy would have be=
en enough to overcome the headwinds in a brutal market, or if we could have=
 raised enough money to continue competing.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Brea=
ther may have failed even if we had kept executing this strategy. It was a =
competitive market and our competitors were willing to spend like drunken s=
ailors. Good strategy, even paired with strong execution, isn&#8217;t a gua=
rantee of success.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>But strong execution </=
span><em>without</em><span> a good strategy is a road to nowhere in an F1 c=
ar.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Don&#8217;t ignore strategy. Re=
ad </span><em><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/46f2f7e2-b9e8-413=
5-98a1-4a30a8d16b69?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8=
-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underlin=
e;">Good Strategy Bad Strategy</a><span>, </span><a href=3D"https://link.sb=
stck.com/redirect/2a10f313-693f-439e-a057-28aaff0bf701?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3Qi=
fQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64,=
 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">7 Powers</a><span>, </span></em><spa=
n>and </span><em><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/e6449980-e625-=
4aba-aaf7-1adb35911496?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqO=
sa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: under=
line;">Productive Uncertainty</a><span>.</span></em><span> Take the time to=
 honestly diagnose the situation, come up with a good guiding policy, and f=
ocus your company&#8217;s limited actions so that they build on each other.=
 Keep refreshing it as you learn more. Have fun solving the puzzle.&#160;</=
span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: =
26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Running a startup is going to be hard no matter =
what. Execution is hard. So don't just execute. Plot a course, forge advant=
ages, build strengths. Create something enduring.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb=
(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Stra=
tegy comes down to choices. The first choice is whether or not to have a st=
rategy. Founders can bet on brute force execution alone. Or pair execution =
with strategy to tilt the odds.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">When uncertainty looms=
, strategy lets you see the path before competitors do. It might just give =
you the time you need to succeed. </p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px;"><hr style=3D"background: #e0e0e0; border: none; height: 1px; =
margin: 32px 0; padding: 0;"></div><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font=
-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>Thanks to </span=
><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect/5a00534d-6a1e-4b1f-972a-46279e=
a7e406?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" =
rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">Dan</a><s=
pan> for editing, and to </span><a href=3D"https://link.sbstck.com/redirect=
